definitions.definition: A small, typically rectangular or round, flat, and rigid object upon which things are carried.
examples: I carefully arranged the dishes on the tray and brought it upstairs.
Make sure that tray of eggs is properly loaded.

definitions.definition: ( by extension ) The items on a full tray.
examples: Before long they had consumed a whole tray of shrimp cocktails and sent for another.

definitions.definition: A component of a device into which an item is placed for use in the device's operations.
examples: The CD tray will not open.
The loader is responsible for placing the work on the trays for the plating machines.

definitions.definition: ( computing , graphical user interface , informal ) A notification area used for icons and alerts .
( computing , business ) A type of retail or wholesale packaging for CPUs where the processors are sold in bulk and/or with minimal packaging.
( Australia ) The platform of a truck that supports the load to be hauled.
